    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div type="letter">
                <div type="text">
                    <opener/>
                    <div type="transcription">
                        <p>I quite believe that animals do somehow communicate together; but how they manage to do so I do not at all know.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                
            </div>
            
            
            <div type="footnotes">
                <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is conjectured from the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8477.xml">letter from Arthur Nicols, 20 August 1872</ref> (<hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 20). The context of the quotation is a discussion of Nicols’s ability to predict his own dogs’ behaviour from their expression, and the dogs’ own ability to communicate between themselves, and is introduced by the following words: ‘Some years ago I sent to the late Charles Darwin a number of cases bearing on this subject, and his reply was:’.</note>
                </div>
        
